items.name: Renee Estella
items.description:
Renèe Estella is a model and social media personality with more than 800K followers on Instagram.

1000-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (r3nestella:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, bodysuit with zipper, cleavage, fishnet stockings, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6".

items.name: McLaren M14A Formula One (1970)
items.description:
Training notes:

V0.6 (SDXL) same "cooking" settings as the Ferrari 312 B v0.6 LoRA

V0.4 (SDXL) was trained on 38 imgs (x 4 repeats) with manually reviewed WD14 captions and 152 real 1970s formula one season photos as regularisation images, against sdXL_v10VAEFix model.

V0.2 (SDXL) FAT Bigger 1.7 GB version but generate more realistic images

Anyway for this vehicle I really need a better dataset with more hi-res pics

The McLaren M14A is a Formula One racing car built and raced by McLaren in the 1970 World Championship and the 1971 World Championship.

The M14A was an evolution of the previous M7A and M7C, with the primary change being the rear brakes were mounted inboard instead of outboard. As with the M7, the M14A was powered by a Cosworth DFV V8 and a Hewland 5-speed manual gearbox.

The unfortunate 1970s season began with two second places, one fourth and three retirements for Bruce McLaren and Denny Hulme.

modelVersions.name: v0.6 (SDXL) LAST VERSION
modelVersions.description:
Dataset of 38 hi-res images (x 4 repeats) x 14 epochs with 152 real Formula 1 1970 season photos as regularisation images

  • Scheduler: Cosine - Extra args: "weight_decay=0.01" "decouple=True" "d_coef=2" "use_bias_correction=True" "safeguard_warmup=True"

  • Network Dim: 64 - Network alpha: 1

  • Min SNR gamma: 5

  • Train batch size: 1

  • Clip: 1

上一个应该过拟合了，搞完一时兴奋，都忘了那个我是0.8权重MIDD分层出的，而且模型有点区别。。。那个真人大模型是我没发的残次品大模型。这次的使用应该更方便，但是还是手镯和发饰的问题还是没有解决。

有好用的停云模型请请留言告诉我，让我去下载，谢谢。（我还是没有抽出来，啊！！！！这个池子里根本没有停云！！三月七3个，素裳一个，虎克一个，紫武一个，白露一个，没见到停云，三月七就差一个都满命了。）

这次3600多步炼了一回直接过拟合，又2000步重炼一回，每一个保存的都测试对照一下，发现600步就差不多了，反复对照之后，选了800步的这个。。。停云怎么这么好拟合，感觉脸比衣服之类的拟合一些，要是还有耐心，并且没有寻得好的停云模型，下次删点游戏截图，再炼一次试试。

国内 吐司 模型地址https://tusi.art/models/604681556478520755

以下为机翻

1 Weight is available, orange 2 is used for anime images, and NED new version is used for cubic images. The example images are not selected, and the effect is directly generated.

The last one should be overfitting. I was so excited that I forgot that I was layered by a 0.8 weight MIDD, and the models are a little different... That real person model is a defective model that I haven't sent. This usage should be more convenient, but the issue of bracelets and hair accessories has not been resolved yet.

Please leave a message and let me know if there is a useful Tingyun model available, so that I can download it. Thank you. (I still haven't pulled it out, ah!!! There's no stopping cloud in this pool!! There are three on March 7th, one in Sushang, one in Huke, one in Ziwu, and one in Bailu. I haven't seen stopping cloud, and on March 7th, almost one is dead.)

This time, more than 3600 steps of refining were directly overfitting, and 2000 steps of refining were repeated. Every saved one was tested and compared. It was found that 600 steps was almost enough. After repeated comparison, the 800 step one was chosen... Why is the tingyun so easy to fit? I feel that the face fits better than clothes and other things. If I have patience and haven't found a good tingyun model, I will delete some screenshots of the game next time and try refining it again.

items.name: CROCHETED
items.description:
Crocheted refers to the art and technique of creating fabric using a hooked needle, known as a crochet hook, and yarn or thread. It is a versatile and popular craft that involves interlocking loops of yarn to form various patterns and designs.

Crocheted items can range from clothing and accessories, such as hats, scarves, and gloves, to home decor items like blankets, pillows, and decorative motifs. The possibilities are nearly endless, and crocheters can create a wide range of textures, shapes, and designs using different stitches and techniques.

Crocheting offers a sense of creativity and allows for personal expression through the choice of colors, patterns, and materials. It can be a relaxing and meditative activity, as well as a practical way to produce functional and beautiful items.

The process of crocheting typically involves creating a foundation chain of interconnected loops and then working different stitches to build the fabric. Common crochet stitches include single crochet, double crochet, and treble crochet, among many others. By combining these stitches and varying tension and yarn choices, crocheters can achieve different effects and textures in their work.

Crocheted items are often cherished for their warmth, softness, and handmade quality. They can be customized to fit individual preferences and can be made with a variety of yarn weights and fiber types, including cotton, wool, acrylic, and more.

Crocheting has a rich history and is practiced by people all over the world. It offers a creative outlet for individuals to express their artistic abilities and create unique and personalized items. Whether for practical use or decorative purposes, crocheted creations bring warmth, comfort, and a touch of handmade charm to our lives.

items.name: Rosalina LoHA | 5 Outfits in 1
items.description:
Rosalina LoHA | 5 Outfits in 1

This is a LoHA Lycoris and you need this Extension for this to work. My first LoHA Model and I'm happy with the results. Credits go to @EDG for helping me out. Thank you.

Weight can go from 0.7 up to 1.0. I recommend 0.9. ControlNet will streamline full body shots much easier, or more complex poses. Works with almost every Style, every alternative Outfit, Photorealistic Models and NSFW LoRA's.

The Main triggerword is Rosalina. You can add a second trigger tag like Rosalina_Biker, Rosalina_Casual, Rosalina_OG, Rosalina_StarryNightDress or Rosalina_Striker. You can also only use second trigger word, to give other Char Rosalina's Outfit (see example). If you wanna go for other Outfits for Rosalina, then use Rosalina_Casual, but it's optional.

This will be updated soon with other Outfits from Rosalina. I saw Sommer Outfit and some other Outfits in Mario Kart Tour. This will be included in the next Update.

Trigger Word:

Rosalina

Helping prompt: (Needed sometimes)

one eye covered, hair over one eye, crown

Outfit 1: Biker

Rosalina, Rosalina_Biker

Outfit 2: OG

Rosalina, Rosalina_OG

Outfit 3: StarryNightDress

Rosalina, Rosalina_StarryNightDress

Outfit 4: Striker

Rosalina, Rosalina_Striker

Outfit 5: Other's

Rosalina, Rosalina_Casual

Bonus: Outfit on other Character (Note: Do NOT use Rosalina and you need to adjust weights/prompts)

Rosalina_Striker / Rosalina_StarryNightDress / Rosalina_Biker / Rosalina_OG, (other Char prompt/LoRA)

How to use LoHA's in auto1111:

  • Download LoHA

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoHA and use the triggerword

  • Make sure to change the weight if needed (by default it's :1)

  • Have Fun!

items.name: Zombies
items.description:
The next release of my LoRA monster collection! Zombies!

I've been meaning to release this for a while now, but took me quite some time to find a good balance of: not having the main female character being a zombie too, having detailed zombies while still keeping an anime style in anime models instead of realistic, and having a horror look without going overboard. It can also produce NSFW outputs.

Trigger word: zombie. You should also use it together with multiple boys and/or crowd.

Other tags to modulate the effect: ugly man, glowing eyes, blood, guro, horror or horror \(theme\), black eyes, rotting, undead, etc.

I recommend weight 1.0, but you can increase or decrease depending on desired effect, and CFG 5-8 should be good for most models. See my example images for reference.

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.
